# ── Provider API keys (BYOK) ────────────────────────────────────────────
# Uncomment the ones you use. Each key enables its provider in the model
# picker; requests go directly from the container to that provider.
# You can also add keys later in the UI (Credentials panel) or with:
#   docker compose exec openscience openscience keys add

ANTHROPIC_API_KEY=your-key-here
# OPENAI_API_KEY=sk-...
# OPENROUTER_API_KEY=sk-or-...
# GEMINI_API_KEY=...
# GOOGLE_API_KEY=...

# ── Remote access ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Extra HTTPS origins allowed by OpenScience's Origin guard.
# For Tailscale: your tailnet DNS name (Admin console → DNS),
# e.g. tail1a2b3c.ts.net → allows https://<server>.tail1a2b3c.ts.net
# For your own domain behind a reverse proxy: example.com
# Comma-separated for multiple.
# OPENSCIENCE_CORS_DOMAINS=tail1a2b3c.ts.net

# ── Ports ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Port published on the server's loopback (127.0.0.1:<port> → container).
# Change it if 3000 is taken; remember to match `tailscale serve <port>`.
# OPENSCIENCE_HOST_PORT=3000
